        <h1><u>Round 1:</u> Introduction & Crisis </h1>
        <ol>
            <li>Assignment:-</li>
            <p>The participating teams will be assigned a particular company with which they will proceed in this competition. </p>
            <li>Introduction:-</li>
            <p>The teams will be given detailed though concise information on the company chosen by them. This information document will be comprising company details on all the four domains of it .i.e. Finance, Production, Research and Development along with Sales and Marketing.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Comprehension:-</li>
                <p>The teams have to read the passage thoroughly for each domain which will be followed by short questions corresponding to the respective domain. Answering the questions is compulsory and marks will be awarded for the correct answer*. These scores will affect the team’s final score to be considered for ranking.</p>
                <p><strong>(*Wrong answer won’t result in any negative marking)</strong></p>
            </ul>    
            <li>Crisis Situation:-</li>
            <p>Once the team is done with answering the comprehension question, they’ll be facing their first company crisis question which might be from any domain followed by some probable solutions from our side. After overcoming the particular domain crisis, the chosen option will lead the team to the next crisis question of a different domain.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Marking:-</li>
                <p><strong>There are no wrong answer/solution.</strong> The chosen solution will be marked on the level of correctness and the feasibility in pursuing the chosen solution. Choosing the best answer will fetch the team full point(.i.e 100 points) and choosing the least correct option will fetch 40 points.</p>
            </ul>
            <li>Ranking:-</li>
            <p>The points accumulated by answering the comprehension questions and choosing the appropriate solution the four crises, the final points will decide the team’s ranking in the competition and also will be carried forward in further rounds.  </p>
        </ol>
        <!-- <img src="icons8-expand-arrow-64.png"> -->
